= Research Questions (NV & SM)

We ask whether Google Maps reviews available before an inspection let us rank restaurants by the risk of a non-happy outcome at that inspection.

#strong[RQ1.] Do three summary statistics of the review window, namely review count, mean star rating, and share of low-star reviews, improve ranking over a class-frequency baseline?

#strong[RQ2.] Do structured hygiene flags extracted from review text by an LLM add ranking power on top of those summary statistics?
